import os
import json
import datetime
import numpy as np
import networkx as nx
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

from tqdm import tqdm_notebook
from jinja2 import Environment
from jinja2 import FileSystemLoader
from telethon import TelegramClient
from matplotlib import cm
from matplotlib.colors import to_hex
from networkx.readwrite import json_graph

with tqdm_notebook() as pbar:
    g = nx.DiGraph()
    g.graph["graph"] = {
        "bgcolor":     "#223333",
        "outputorder": "edgesfirst",
        "overlap":     "prism",
        "size":        "20,20!",
        "dpi":         "500"
    }
    
    api_id   = 123456
    api_hash = "0123456789abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv"
    client   = TelegramClient("user", api_id, api_hash)
    client.connect()
    client.start()
    client.session._conn.set_progress_handler(pbar.update, 1)
    channels = [channel.name for channel in client.get_dialogs()]
    for channel in channels:
        try:
            participants = client.get_participants(client.get_entity(channel), limit=100)
        except Exception as e:
            print("{} - {}".format(channel, e))
            continue
        channel = channel.replace(":", "")
        for i, participant in enumerate(participants):
            user = participant.username
            if not user:
                try:
                    user = participant.first_name[:16] + participant.last_name[:16]
                except:
                    continue
            user = user.replace(":", "")
            node = user, channel
            if node[0] and node[1]:
                g.add_edge(*node)
    client.disconnect()

inactive = []
viridis  = plt.get_cmap("viridis", 80)
colormap = plt.get_cmap("gist_heat", 80)
maxoutdg = max([d for n, d in g.out_degree()])
for n in g.nodes():
    active = g.in_degree[n] > 1 or g.out_degree[n] > 2
    group  = g.in_degree[n] > 1
    if not active:
        inactive.append(n)
        continue
    norm  = (g.out_degree[n]-1.25) / ((maxoutdg*1.3)-1.25)
    color = colormap(norm)[:3]
    color = viridis(np.random.randint(80))[:3] if group else color
    tint  = tuple([min(c*1.3, 1.0) for c in color])
    label = "{} - {}".format(n, g.in_degree[n] if group else g.out_degree[n])
    label = label    if active else ""
    width = 1.5*norm if active else 0.05
    width = 3 if group else width
    g.node[n].update({
        "label":     label,
        "active":    active,
        "group":     group,
        "width":     width,
        "color":     to_hex(tint), #border color
        "fillcolor": to_hex(color),
        "shape":     "circle",
        "style":     "filled",
        "fontsize":  "10",
        "fontname":  "arial bold",
        "fontcolor": "#FFFFFF",
        "fixedsize": "true" })
    if not group:
        for edge in g.out_edges(n):
            g.edges[edge].update({"color": to_hex(tint+(norm,), keep_alpha=True)})#,"arrowhead":"none"})

g.remove_nodes_from(inactive)
date = datetime.datetime.now()

print("Building graph for {} participants.".format(len(g.nodes())-len(channels)))
with open("{}_network.html".format(date.strftime("%Y%m%d-%H%M%S")), "w") as f:
    template = Environment(
        loader=FileSystemLoader(""),
        trim_blocks=True).get_template("template.html")
    f.write(template.render(graph=json.dumps(json_graph.node_link_data(g), indent=4)))
    
nx.drawing.nx_pydot.write_dot(g, open("map.dot", "w", encoding="utf-8"))
os.system('"sfdp.exe -q -Tpng map.dot > network_{}.png"'.format(date.strftime("%Y%m%d-%H%M%S")))

html = \ # template.html
"""
<!DOCTYPE html>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<script src="https://d3js.org/d3.v4.min.js"></script>
<body></body>
<script>
var graph = {{ graph }};
</script>
<script>
var width  = window.innerWidth-20;
var height = window.innerHeight-20;

var out = d3.select("body").append("textarea")
    .style("position", "absolute")
    .style("height", "18px")
    .style("resize", "none")
    .style("color", "#fff")
    .style("background", graph.graph.graph.bgcolor);

var svg = d3.select("body").append("svg")
    .attr("width",  width)
    .attr("height", height);

svg.append("rect")
    .attr("width",  width)
    .attr("height", height)
    .style("fill", graph.graph.graph.bgcolor)
    .style("pointer-events", "all");

var container = svg.append("g");

svg.call(d3.zoom()
    .scaleExtent([0.1, 7])
    .on("zoom", function() {
        container.attr("transform", d3.event.transform);
    }));

var simulation = d3.forceSimulation()
    .force("link",      d3.forceLink().id(function(d) { return d.id; }).strength(0.25))
    .force("charge",    d3.forceManyBody())
    .force("center",    d3.forceCenter(width / 2, height / 2))
    .force('collision', d3.forceCollide().radius(20))
    .nodes(graph.nodes)
    .on("tick", ticked);

simulation.force("link")
    .links(graph.links);

var unique = {};
var colors = [];
graph.nodes.forEach(function(d) {
    if (!unique[d.fillcolor]) {
        colors.push(d.fillcolor);
        unique[d.fillcolor] = true;
    }
});

var markers = svg.append("svg:defs").selectAll("marker")
    .data(colors)
    .enter().append("svg:marker")
    .attr("id", function(d) { return d.replace("#",""); })
    .attr("viewBox", "0 -5 10 10")
    .attr("refX", 10)
    .attr("refY", -1.5)
    .attr("markerWidth", 6)
    .attr("markerHeight", 6)
    .attr("orient", "auto")
    .append("svg:path")
    .attr("d", "M0,-5L10,0L0,5")
    .style("fill", function(d) { return d; });

var link = container.selectAll(".link")
    .data(graph.links)
    .enter().append("path")
        .attr("class", "link")
        .attr("stroke", function(d) { return d.color; })
        .attr("stroke-opacity", 0.5)
        .attr("marker-end", "url()");

var node = container.selectAll(".node")
    .data(graph.nodes)
    .enter().append("g")
        .attr("class", "node")
        .on("click", function(d) {
            out.property("value", d.label);
            out.node().focus();
            out.node().select();
            document.execCommand("copy");
            window.getSelection().removeAllRanges();
        })
        .on("mouseover", function(d) {
            node.style("fill-opacity", function(o) {
                    return neighboring(d, o) ? 1 : 0.05;
                });
            link
                .style("stroke-opacity", function(o) {
                    return o.source === d || o.target === d ? 1 : 0.05;
                })
                .style("marker-end", function(o) {
                    return o.source === d || o.target === d ? "url("+o.source.fillcolor+")" : "url()";
                });
        })
        .on("mouseout", function(d) {
            node.style("fill-opacity",   1);
            link.style("stroke-opacity", 0.5)
                .style("marker-end", "url()");
        });

node.append("circle")
    .attr("r",    function(d) { d.radius = d.width*10+5; return d.radius; })
    .attr("fill", function(d) { return d.fillcolor; });

node.append("text")
    .text(function (d) { return d.label; })
        .style("text-anchor", "middle")
        .style("fill",        function(d) { return d.fontcolor; })
        .style("font-family", function(d) { return d.fontname; })
        .style("font-size",   function(d) { return d.fontsize; })
        .style("pointer-events", "none");

function ticked() {
    link.attr("d", function(d) {
        diffX    = d.target.x - d.source.x;
        diffY    = d.target.y - d.source.y;
        distance = Math.sqrt((diffX * diffX) + (diffY * diffY));
        offsetX  = (diffX * d.target.radius) / distance;
        offsetY  = (diffY * d.target.radius) / distance;
        return "M" + d.source.x + "," + d.source.y + "L" + (d.target.x - offsetX) + "," + (d.target.y - offsetY);
    });
    
    node.attr("transform", function (d) {return "translate(" + d.x + ", " + d.y + ")";});
}

var linkedByIndex = {};
graph.links.forEach(function(d) {
    linkedByIndex[d.source.index + "," + d.target.index] = 1;
});

function neighboring(a, b) {
    return linkedByIndex[a.index + "," + b.index] || linkedByIndex[b.index + "," + a.index] || a.index == b.index;
}
</script>
"""
